            <title>[OWB-1069] Propagate SessionContext to end of request only if a manual Session.invalidate() was called</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OWB-1069</link>
                <project id="12310844" key="OWB">OpenWebBeans</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The CDI spec defines that a Session needs to be&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;destroyed immediately on a session timeout&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;destroyed at the end of the request if a manual Session.invalidate() got invoked.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This is pretty hard to detect as the session enviction also gets invoked at the begin of a request but only &lt;em&gt;after&lt;/em&gt; the sessionInitialized events got fired.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
